(6) The office of the Director-General becomes vacant if the Director-General — (a) dies; (b) becomes legally disqualified ; (c) resigns by a written notice of three months addressed to the President; (d) is adjudged bankrupt; or (e) is convicted of an offence and sentenced to imprisonment for a period of not less than six months without the option of a fine.
