(2) The documents used by a procuring entity under subsection (1) shall contain sufficient information to allow fairness, equity, transparency, efficiency, cost-effectiveness and competition among persons who intend to participate in the procurement process.
The documents used by a procuring entity under subsection (1) shall contain sufficient information to allow fairness, equity, transparency, efficiency, cost-effectiveness and competition among persons who intend to participate in the procurement process.
